cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.SD 

The paper proposes a deep learning approach to predict the short-term power output of a photovoltaic panel using sky images. This involves computer vision techniques to estimate weather conditions from the images, and deep learning models to learn the relationship between sky appearance and power output. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves training and evaluating different neural network architectures, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep learning for prediction tasks falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves data analysis and processing, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with energy management and smart grids, which falls under cs.SD (Systems and Control).
